# Character Type Casting

Characters are stored internally as Unicode values.

Example

```java
char c = 'A';

int value = c;

System.out.println(value);
```

Output

```
65
```

---

# Integer to Character

```java
int value = 66;

char c = (char)value;

System.out.println(c);
```

Output

```
B
```

