# String Concatenation

When one operand is a `String`, the `+` operator performs string concatenation.

---

## Example 1

```java
System.out.println("Java" + 10 + 20);
```

Output

```
Java1020
```

Evaluation

```
"Java" + 10

↓

Java10

↓

Java10 + 20

↓

Java1020
```

---

## Example 2

```java
System.out.println(10 + 20 + "Java");
```

Output

```
30Java
```

Evaluation

```
10 + 20

↓

30

↓

30 + "Java"

↓

30Java
```

