# Choosing the Correct Data Type (DSA)

Always read the problem constraints before selecting a data type.

Example

If

```
n ≤ 10⁹
```

Use

```java
int n;
```

---

If

```
n ≤ 10¹⁸
```

Use

```java
long n;
```

Using an incorrect data type can cause overflow and produce wrong answers.

