# Common Interview Mistakes

❌

```java
byte c = a + b;
```

Compilation Error.

---

✅

```java
int c = a + b;
```

or

```java
byte c = (byte)(a + b);
```

---

❌ Thinking Java rounds decimals during narrowing.

Example

```java
(int)99.99
```

Output

```
99
```

Java truncates the fractional part.

---

❌ Assuming characters are stored directly as letters.

Characters are stored internally as Unicode values.

---

❌ Ignoring problem constraints while choosing data types.

Always select a data type that can store the maximum possible value.

